由于火星与[[地球|地球]]既相近又相似，因此，火星上是否可能存在生命一直是[[天体生物学|天体生物学]]关注的一个主题。迄今为止，尚未在[[火星|火星]]上发现曾经或现在的[[生命|生命]]的证据。累积的证据表明，在古代[[诺亚纪|诺亚纪]]时期，火星表面环境有液态水，并可能适合[[微生物|微生物]][[行星适居性|居住]]，但宜居的条件并不一定代表就有生命<ref name="NYT-20200724">{{cite news |last=Ferreira |first=Becky |title=3 Great Mysteries About Life on Mars - How habitable was early Mars? Why did it become less hospitable? And could there be life there now? |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/07/24/science/mars-life-water.html |date=2020-07-24 |work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]] |access-date=2020-07-24 |archive-date=2022-01-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220104105810/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/07/24/science/mars-life-water.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="NYT-20160912">{{cite news|last=Chang |first=Kenneth |title=Visions of Life on Mars in Earth's Depths |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/09/13/science/south-african-mine-life-on-mars.html |date=2016-09-12 |work=[[Financial_Times|Financial Times]] |access-date=2016-09-12 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160912225220/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/09/13/science/south-african-mine-life-on-mars.html |archive-date=2016-09-12 }}</ref>。

对生命证据的科学探索始于19世纪，直到今天，通过望远镜调查和部署的探测器仍在继续进行。早期的研究主要侧重于现象学并近乎幻想，而现代的科学研究则强调寻找[[水|水]]、行星表面土壤和岩石中的化学[[生命印迹|生命印迹]]以及大气层中的[[生物标记|生物标记]]气体<ref>{{cite conference|url=https://ntrs.nasa.gov/search.jsp?R=20120003707 |title=The Search for Life on Mars |last=Mumma |first=Michael J. |date=2012-01-08 |conference=Origin of Life Gordon Research Conference |location=Galveston, TX |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160604111239/https://ntrs.nasa.gov/search.jsp?R=20120003707 |archive-date=2016-06-04 }}</ref>。

由于与早期地球相似，火星令人感兴趣的是对[[生命起源|生命起源]]的研究，尤其是它寒冷的气候和缺乏[[板块构造论|板块构造]]或[[大陆漂移学说|大陆漂移]]，自[[赫斯珀里亚纪|赫斯珀里亚纪]]末期以来，几乎就一直没有变化，全球至少三分之二的地表年龄已超过35亿年。因此，火星可能拥有最佳的生命起源前条件记录，即使那里没有或从未存在过生命<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1029/RG027i002p00189 |title=The early environment and its evolution on Mars: Implication for life |date=1989 |last1=McKay |first1=Christopher P. |last2=Stoker |first2=Carol R. |journal=Reviews of Geophysics |volume=27 |issue=2 |pages=189–214 |bibcode=1989RvGeo..27..189M |type=Submitted manuscript |url=https://zenodo.org/record/1231452 |access-date=2021-11-18 |archive-date=2021-11-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211118130129/https://zenodo.org/record/1231452 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Fromproto">{{cite journal |bibcode=2007prpl.conf..929G |arxiv=astro-ph/0602008 |title=From Protoplanets to Protolife: The Emergence and Maintenance of Life |url=https://archive.org/details/arxiv-astro-ph0602008 |last1=Gaidos |first1=Eric |last2=Selsis |first2=Franck |date=2007 |pages=929–44 |journal=Protostars and Planets V}}</ref>，而生命可能早在44.8亿年前就已开始演化<ref>{{cite journal |title=Decline of giant impacts on Mars by 4.48 billion years ago and an early opportunity for habitability |date=2019 |last1=Moser |first1=D. E. |last2=Arcuri |first2=G. A. |last3=Reinhard |first3=D. A. |last4=White |first4=L. F. |last5=Darling |first5=J. R. |last6=Barker |first6=I. R. |last7=Larson |first7=D. J. |last8=Irving |first8=A. J. |last9=McCubbin |first9=F. M. |last10=Tait |first10=K. T. |last11=Roszjar |first11=J. |last12=Wittmann |first12=A. |last13=Davis |first13=C. |journal=Nature Geoscience |volume=12 |issue=7 |pages=522–527 |bibcode=2019NatGe..12..522M |doi=10.1038/s41561-019-0380-0 |url=https://researchportal.port.ac.uk/portal/en/publications/decline-of-giant-impacts-on-mars-by-448-billion-years-ago-and-an-early-opportunity-for-habitability(87d6a7fa-4a74-4507-9f84-feb6b8492c2f).html |doi-access=free |access-date=2021-11-18 |archive-date=2021-06-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210628195845/https://researchportal.port.ac.uk/portal/en/publications/decline-of-giant-impacts-on-mars-by-448-billion-years-ago-and-an-early-opportunity-for-habitability(87d6a7fa-4a74-4507-9f84-feb6b8492c2f).html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

在确认过去存在过地表液态水之后，[[好奇号|好奇号]]、[[毅力号火星探测器|毅力号]]和[[机遇号火星漫游车|机遇号]]探测车开始寻找过去生命的证据，包括过去基于[[自养生物|自养]]、[[化能生物|化能]]或化能自养菌[[生物圈|生物圈]]，以及涵盖[[湖积平原|湖积平原]]在内的古代宜居性水环境（与古代河流或湖泊有关的[[平原|平原]]）<ref name="SCI-20140124a">{{cite journal|last=Grotzinger |first=John P. |title=Introduction to Special Issue - Habitability, Taphonomy, and the Search for Organic Carbon on Mars |journal=[[Science_(journal)|Science]] |date=2014-01-24 |volume=343 |issue=6169 |pages=386–387 |doi=10.1126/science.1249944 |bibcode=2014Sci...343..386G |pmid=24458635 |doi-access=free }}</ref><ref name="SCI-20140124special">{{cite journal|author=Various |title=Special Issue - Table of Contents - Exploring Martian Habitability |url=http://www.sciencemag.org/content/343/6169.toc#SpecialIssue |date=2014-01-24 |journal=[[Science_(journal)|Science]] |volume=343 |number=6169 |pages=345–452 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140129042127/http://www.sciencemag.org/content/343/6169.toc |archive-date=2014-01-29 }}</ref><ref name="SCI-20140124">{{cite journal|author=Various |title=Special Collection - Curiosity - Exploring Martian Habitability |url=http://www.sciencemag.org/site/extra/curiosity/ |date=2014-01-24 |journal=[[Science_(journal)|Science]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140128102653/http://www.sciencemag.org/site/extra/curiosity/ |archive-date=2014-01-28 }}</ref><ref name="SCI-20140124c">{{cite journal|title=A Habitable Fluvio-Lacustrine Environment at Yellowknife Bay, Gale Crater, Mars |date=2014-01-24 |journal=[[Science_(journal)|Science]] |volume=343 |issue=6169 |page=1242777 |doi=10.1126/science.1242777 |last1=Grotzinger |first1=J. P. |last2=Sumner |first2=D. Y. |last3=Kah |first3=L. C. |last4=Stack |first4=K. |last5=Gupta |first5=S. |last6=Edgar |first6=L. |last7=Rubin |first7=D. |last8=Lewis |first8=K. |last9=Schieber |first9=J. |last10=Mangold |first10=N. |last11=Milliken |first11=R. |last12=Conrad |first12=P. G. |last13=Desmarais |first13=D. |last14=Farmer |first14=J. |last15=Siebach |first15=K. |last16=Calef |first16=F. |last17=Hurowitz |first17=J. |last18=McLennan |first18=S. M. |last19=Ming |first19=D. |last20=Vaniman |first20=D. |last21=Crisp |first21=J. |last22=Vasavada |first22=A. |last23=Edgett |first23=K. S. |last24=Malin |first24=M. |last25=Blake |first25=D. |last26=Gellert |first26=R. |last27=Mahaffy |first27=P. |last28=Wiens |first28=R. C. |last29=Maurice |first29=S. |last30=Grant |first30=J. A. |display-authors=9 |bibcode=2014Sci...343A.386G |pmid=24324272 |citeseerx=10.1.1.455.3973 |s2cid=52836398 }}</ref>。目前，[[美国宇航局|美国宇航局]]和[[欧洲空间局|欧洲空间局]]的主要目标是寻找火星上宜居性、[[埋藏学|埋藏学]](与[[化石|化石]]有关)和[[有机化合物|有机化合物]]的证据。

火星沉积岩内有机化合物和[[硼|硼]]的发现令人振奋，因为它们是[[生命起源|生命起源]]前的化学前体。这些发现，连同先前有关火星古代明显存在液态水的证据，进一步支持了火星[[盖尔撞击坑|盖尔撞击坑]]早期可能的宜居性 <ref name="GPL-20170905">{{cite journal |author=Gasda, Patrick J. |display-authors=etal |title=In situ detection of boron by ChemCam on Mars |date=2017-09-05 |journal=[[Geophysical_Research_Letters|Geophysical Research Letters]] |doi=10.1002/2017GL074480 |bibcode=2017GeoRL..44.8739G |volume=44 |issue=17 |pages=8739–8748 |url=https://authors.library.caltech.edu/82117/2/grl56315-sup-0001-2017GL074480-SI.pdf |doi-access=free |access-date=2021-11-18 |archive-date=2021-11-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211116185025/https://authors.library.caltech.edu/82117/2/grl56315-sup-0001-2017GL074480-SI.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="GZ-20170906">{{cite news |last=Paoletta |first=Rae |title=Curiosity Has Discovered Something That Raises More Questions About Life on Mars |url=https://gizmodo.com/curiosity-has-discovered-something-that-raises-more-que-1800879035 |date=2017-09-06 |work=[[Gizmodo|Gizmodo]] |access-date=2017-09-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170906222116/http://gizmodo.com/curiosity-has-discovered-something-that-raises-more-que-1800879035 |archive-date=2017-09-06 |url-status=live  }}</ref> 。目前，火星表面充斥着[[电离辐射|电离辐射]]，[[火星土壤|火星土壤]]富含对[[微生物|微生物]]有毒的[[高氯酸盐|高氯酸盐]] <ref name="SM-20170706">{{cite news |last=Daley |first=Jason |title=Mars Surface May Be Too Toxic for Microbial Life - The combination of UV radiation and perchlorates common on Mars could be deadly for bacteria|url=http://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/mars-surface-may-be-toxic-bacteria-180963966/ |date=2017-07-06 |work=[[Smithsonian_(magazine)|Smithsonian]] |access-date=2017-07-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170709052855/http://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/mars-surface-may-be-toxic-bacteria-180963966/
|archive-date=2017-07-09 |url-status=live  }}</ref><ref name="NAT-20170706">{{cite journal|last1=Wadsworth |first1=Jennifer |last2=Cockell |first2=Charles S.
|title=Perchlorates on Mars enhance the bacteriocidal effects of UV light
|date=2017-07-06 |journal=[[Scientific_Reports|Scientific Reports]] |volume=7 |page=4662 |number=4662
|doi=10.1038/s41598-017-04910-3 |bibcode = 2017NatSR...7.4662W |pmid=28684729 |pmc=5500590}}</ref>。因此，人们一致认为，如果火星上存在生命，则最有可能发现或保存于地表下，远离现今严酷的表面环境。

2018年6月，美国宇航局宣布检测到火星上[[甲烷|甲烷]]浓度的季节性变化，甲烷可由微生物或地质方式产生<ref name="NASA-20180607">{{cite web |last1=Brown |first1=Dwayne |last2=Wendel |first2=JoAnna |last3=Steigerwald |first3=Bill |last4=Jones |first4=Nancy |last5=Good |first5=Andrew |title=Release 18-050 - NASA Finds Ancient Organic Material, Mysterious Methane on Mars |url=https://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-finds-ancient-organic-material-mysterious-methane-on-mars |date=2018-06-07 |work=[[NASA|NASA]] |access-date=2018-06-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180607181653/https://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-finds-ancient-organic-material-mysterious-methane-on-mars/ |archive-date=2018-06-07 |url-status=live  }}</ref>。欧洲[[火星微量气体任务卫星|火星微量气体任务卫星]]自2018年4月开始绘制大气层甲烷分布图，2022年[[ExoMars|火星太空生物]]探测车[[罗莎琳·富兰克林号|罗莎琳·富兰克林号]]将钻探和分析地下样品，而美国宇航局[[火星2020|火星2020]]探测车[[毅力号火星探测器|毅力号]]已成功着陆，它将储存数十份钻孔样本，以便在21世纪20年代末或21世纪30年代将其运回至地球实验室。截至2021年2月8日，已报告了在[[金星|金星]]（通过[[磷化氢|磷化氢]]）和火星（通过[[甲烷|甲烷]]）上可能发现的生命形式的最新研究状况<ref name="NYT-20210208">{{cite news |last1=Chang |first1=Kenneth |last2=Stirone |first2=Shannon |title=Life on Venus? The Picture Gets Cloudier - Despite doubts from many scientists, a team of researchers who said they had detected an unusual gas in the planet's atmosphere were still confident of their findings. |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/02/08/science/venus-life-phosphine.html |date=2021-02-08 |work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]] |access-date=2021-02-08 |archive-date=2022-01-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220108101055/https://www.nytimes.com/2021/02/08/science/venus-life-phosphine.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

