火星上的水几乎完全以水冰的形式存在，位于[[火星极冠|火星极地冰盖]]和火星浅表面之下，甚至在更温和的纬度<ref name="mars.jpl.nasa.gov">{{cite web|url=http://mars.jpl.nasa.gov/odyssey/newsroom/pressreleases/20020528a.html |title=Mars Odyssey: Newsroom |publisher=Mars.jpl.nasa.gov |date=2002-05-28 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110606235941/http://mars.jpl.nasa.gov/odyssey/newsroom/pressreleases/20020528a.html |archive-date=2011-06-06 }}</ref><ref name="Feildman, T. 2004">{{cite journal |bibcode=2004JGRE..10909006F |doi=10.1029/2003JE002160 |title=Global distribution of near-surface hydrogen on Mars |date=2004 |last=Feldman |first=W. C. |journal=Journal of Geophysical Research |volume=109|doi-access=free }}</ref>。[[火星大气层|大气层]]中也存在少量的水气<ref name="ucar">{{cite web |url=http://www.windows.ucar.edu/tour/link=/mars/exploring/MGS_water_clouds.html |title=Mars Global Surveyor Measures Water Clouds |access-date=2009-03-07 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090812084157/http://www.windows.ucar.edu/tour/link%3D/mars/exploring/MGS_water_clouds.html |archive-date=2009-08-12 }}</ref>，但火星表面没有液态水体，因为火星表面平均大气压为600[[帕斯卡|帕斯卡]]（0.087磅/平方英寸）—大约只是地球海平面平均气压的0.6%，并且温度太低（210 K，摄氏零下63度），会导致液态水瞬间冻结。尽管如此，但在大约38亿年前<ref name="Baker">{{cite journal |bibcode=1991Natur.352..589B |title=Ancient oceans, ice sheets and the hydrological cycle on Mars |last1=Baker |first1=V. R. |last2=Strom |first2=R. G. |last3=Gulick |first3=V. C. |last4=Kargel |first4=J. S. |last5=Komatsu |first5=G. |volume=352 |date=1991 |pages=589–594 |journal=Nature |doi=10.1038/352589a0 |last6=Kale |first6=V. S. |issue=6336|s2cid=4321529 }}</ref>，[[火星大气层|火星大气层]]更稠密，温度也更高，地表上流淌着包括大型海洋<ref>"Mapping Mars: Science, Imagination and the Birth of a World". Oliver Morton, 2002. {{ISBN|0-312-24551-3}}{{page needed|date=June 2013}}</ref><ref name="Sea">{{cite web|url=http://www.psrd.hawaii.edu/July03/MartianSea.html |title=PSRD: Ancient Floodwaters and Seas on Mars |publisher=Psrd.hawaii.edu |date=2003-07-16 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110104093144/http://www.psrd.hawaii.edu/July03/MartianSea.html |archive-date=2011-01-04 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.spaceref.com/news/viewpr.html?pid=26947 |title=Gamma-Ray Evidence Suggests Ancient Mars Had Oceans |publisher=SpaceRef |date=2008-11-17 }}</ref><ref name="2003JGRE..108.5042C">{{cite journal |bibcode=2003JGRE..108.5042C |title=Oceans on Mars: An assessment of the observational evidence and possible fate |last1=Carr |first1=Michael H. |last2=Head |first2=James W. |volume=108 |issue=E5 |date=2003 |page=5042 |journal=Journal of Geophysical Research: Planets |doi=10.1029/2002JE001963}}</ref><ref name="SFN-20130125">{{cite web|last=Harwood |first=William |title=Opportunity rover moves into 10th year of Mars operations |url=http://www.spaceflightnow.com/news/n1301/25opportunity/ |date=2013-01-25 |publisher=Space Flight Now |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131224095028/http://www.spaceflightnow.com/news/n1301/25opportunity/ |archive-date=2013-12-24 }}</ref>在内的大量液态水<ref name="flashback">{{cite web|url=http://www.space.com/scienceastronomy/flashback-water-on-mars-announced-10-years-ago-100622.html |title=Flashback: Water on Mars Announced 10 Years Ago |publisher=SPACE.com |date=2000-06-22 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101222210332/http://www.space.com/scienceastronomy/flashback-water-on-mars-announced-10-years-ago-100622.html |archive-date=2010-12-22 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://science.nasa.gov/headlines/y2001/ast05jan_1.htm |work=Science@NASA |title=The Case of the Missing Mars Water |access-date=2009-03-07 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090327234049/https://science.nasa.gov/headlines/y2001/ast05jan_1.htm |archive-date=2009-03-27  }}</ref><ref name="Clay clues">{{cite news|title=Mars Rover Opportunity Examines Clay Clues in Rock |date=2013-05-17 |publisher=Jet Propulsion Laboratory |url=http://www.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news.php?release=2013-167 |work=NASA |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130611181547/http://www.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news.php?release=2013-167 |archive-date=2013-06-11 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=NASA Rover Helps Reveal Possible Secrets of Martian Life |date=2005-11-29 |url=http://www.nasa.gov/home/hqnews/2005/nov/HQ_05415_rover_secrets_prt.htm |work=NASA |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131122193015/http://www.nasa.gov/home/hqnews/2005/nov/HQ_05415_rover_secrets_prt.htm |archive-date=2013-11-22 }}</ref>。[[File:History_of_Water_on_Mars.jpg|thumb]]
